<br>
 For example, I was the main healer in a group of 4 in Merus with a ranger , pally and wiz. The ranger was getting hit so much I drained my mana pool on him every pull. Once he switched to attacking from behind, the mob stayed focussed on the pally and he was getting hit about 1/3 as often. In Kael arena and in Umbral the mobs tended to move quite a bit and back into walls so the box technique was usefull in keeping them centered and allowed for a quicker kill.<br>
<br>
 I agree , though, that the higher level game may require adjustments or alterations to tactics as you pointed out in the case of the hasted ranger. <br>
<br>
